climbs.name: The Great Big Car Jack Off

content.description:
WARNING: Please keep off, crag is still under development. There may still be loose rocks and dirt on new climbs. This entry is for historical purposes only till the crag is open.

NOTE: A car jack was used multiple times to clean this route.

Start up the lower steep section on jugs, upper part of the 1st pitch has a technical crux. If the proper sequence and holds are found it is 5.10a, if not then it can get into 5.11 territory quickly. Tricky onsight for the grade.

2nd is an enjoyable 5.7 with a slab crux.

Can be done as a single pitch with a 60m but with rope stretch the second cannot fall on the start of the first pitch.

The FA party did it both ways, as a single and multi pitch.

2 30m raps will get you down.



To be updated.

Bring 12+ draws plus anchor if doing as 2 pitches. 22+ draws if done as a single pitch.
This will be updated when the crag is completed. At present routes are still being developed. For now this is a record for the FA as they get completed.
